                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2904: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-31T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1320. Repeat to London your 1463, July 29th noon and present telegram. Suggest to
                    Foreign Office that announcement be deferred a few days. The Department has not
                    yet been informed whether British and Japanese Governments will make
                    announcement as suggested. You will be promptly notified of the decision of
                    these two Governments in order that the announcement may be made
                    simultaneously.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
